  "local_port": 36074,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My laptop is showing limited connectivity to WiFi while other on other laptop working properly?",
  "response": "If one laptop is showing limited connectivity to WiFi while another is working properly, there could be several reasons behind the issue. Here are a few troubleshooting steps you can take:\n\n1. **Restart Your Laptop:** Sometimes a simple restart can fix connectivity issues.\n\n2. **Forget and Reconnect to the Network:**\n   - Go to WiFi settings on your laptop.\n   - Find the network you are trying to connect to.\n   - Select \"Forget Network\".\n   - Restart your laptop and then try reconnecting to the WiFi.\n\n3. **Update Network Drivers:**\n   - Go to Device Manager by typing it into the search bar.\n   - Find your network adapter under \u201cNetwork adapters\u201d.\n   - Right-click on the network adapter and select \u201cUpdate driver\u201d.\n\n4. **Check the WiFi Signal:**\n   - Ensure you are within range of the router.\n   - Try moving closer to see if the signal improves.\n\n5. **Reset the Router:**\n   - Unplug the router and wait for about 10-15 seconds.\n   - Plug it back in and wait for it to restart.\n\n6. **Check Network Configuration:**\n   - Open Command Prompt (you can find it by searching in the Start menu).\n   - Type `ipconfig /release` and then `ipconfig /renew`.\n   - Check if the issue is resolved.\n\n7. **Check for Interference:**\n   - Other devices or appliances like microwaves or cordless phones can cause interference.\n   - Try changing the WiFi channel from the router settings.\n\n8. **Disable Power Saving Mode:**\n   - Go to Device Manager.\n   - Right-click on your network adapter and select \"Properties\".\n   - Go to the \"Power Management\" tab.\n   - Uncheck \"Allow the computer to turn off this device to save power\".\n\n9. **Check for Malware or Viruses:**\n   - Run a full system scan using your antivirus software.\n\n10. **Contact Your Internet Service Provider (ISP):**\n    - There might be an issue with the connection that requires ISP assistance.\n\nIf you've tried all these steps and the problem persists, there might be a hardware issue with your laptop's network adapter. In that case, seeking professional help might be necessary.",
